(42, 8, 44, 39, 4, 2, 2, NULL, 'Healing and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize healing as a significant theme. In Luke, the woman''s healing occurs through a touch, while Malachi speaks of healing arising with the Sun of righteousness. This connection highlights the transformative power of divine healing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 44, 44, 19, 12, 12, 'touched the border of his garment', 'Healing Through Touch', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing through physical contact. Both passages emphasize the power of touch, as seen in the woman touching Jesus'' garment and the handkerchiefs from Paul healing the sick.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 44, 2, 15, 26, 26, NULL, 'Healing and Divine Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing in both passages. In Luke, the woman''s issue of blood is healed by touching Jesus, while Exodus emphasizes God as the one who heals diseases.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 44, 40, 8, 3, 3, 'touched', 'Healing Touch of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the act of Jesus touching individuals to bring about healing. In Luke, the woman touches the border of his garment, while in Matthew, Jesus touches the leper directly, resulting in immediate healing.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 44, 40, 20, 34, 34, 'touched', 'Healing Touch of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the immediate healing that occurs when individuals touch Jesus. The act of touching leads to miraculous results, showcasing Jesus'' power to heal.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 45, 42, 9, 13, 13, NULL, 'Connection of Need and Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of addressing needs in the midst of a crowd. In both passages, Jesus responds to the pressing demands of the people, whether through healing or providing food.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 45, 41, 5, 30, 32, 'Who touched me?', 'Connection of Touch and Recognition', 'Both passages emphasize the act of touching Jesus and the subsequent inquiry about who did so. They highlight the disciples'' confusion regarding the multitude pressing against Jesus while he seeks to identify the individual who touched him.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 45, 42, 5, 5, 5, NULL, 'Faith in Jesus'' Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the response of faith to Jesus'' authority. In Luke 8:45, the act of touching Jesus signifies belief in His power, while in Luke 5:5, Simon Peter''s willingness to let down the net reflects trust in Jesus'' command despite prior failure.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 46, 42, 6, 19, 19, 'virtue is gone out of me', 'Connection of Healing Virtue', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''virtue'' going out from Jesus, indicating His healing power. In Luke 8:46, Jesus acknowledges that virtue has left Him due to a touch, while in Luke 6:19, it is noted that virtue went out of Him to heal the multitude.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 46, 42, 5, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Healing Power', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of healing power associated with Jesus. In Luke 8:46, the virtue that has gone out of Jesus indicates his ability to heal, while Luke 5:17 states that the power of the Lord was present to heal. This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' healing ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 46, 60, 2, 9, 9, 'virtue is gone out of me', 'Connection of Healing and Calling', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation through divine interaction. In Luke, the ''virtue'' that leaves Jesus signifies healing and empowerment, while 1 Peter speaks of being called into ''marvellous light,'' indicating a transformative experience.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 41, 5, 33, 33, NULL, 'Connection of Fear and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the woman''s fear and trembling as she approaches Jesus to reveal her healing. This shared emotional response highlights her vulnerability and the significance of her encounter with him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 42, 17, 15, 16, NULL, 'Expressions of Gratitude for Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of falling down before Jesus in gratitude after healing. The woman in Luke 8:47 declares her healing publicly, while the Samaritan in Luke 17:15-16 returns to thank Jesus, highlighting the importance of acknowledging divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 46, 2, 3, 3, 'trembling', 'Connection of Trembling and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of trembling in the presence of Jesus. The woman in Luke expresses her fear and vulnerability when she approaches Jesus, while Paul in Corinthians describes his own state of weakness and fear when with the Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 9, 16, 4, 4, 'trembling', 'Trembling Before Divine Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of trembling in response to divine authority. In both passages, individuals express fear and reverence when confronted with God''s power, whether through Jesus'' healing or Samuel''s arrival.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 44, 16, 29, 29, 'came trembling, and falling down before', 'Trembling and Falling Down', 'Both passages emphasize the act of trembling and falling down before a figure of authority. In Luke, the woman falls before Jesus after her healing, while in Acts, the jailer falls before Paul and Silas, indicating a response of reverence and fear.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 47, 7, 15, 15, NULL, 'Fear and Trembling Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear and trembling in both passages. The woman in Luke expresses her fear when approaching Jesus, while the Corinthians demonstrate their fear and trembling in receiving him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 47, 19, 2, 11, 11, 'trembling', 'Fear and Trembling in Worship', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear and trembling in both passages. The woman in Luke approaches Jesus with trembling, while Psalms encourages serving the Lord with fear and rejoicing with trembling.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
